                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The dragon is critically hit by a melee weapon without reach or an unarmed attack that deals slashing or piercing damage</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> A gout of blood spurts from the dragon's wound and instantaneously calcifies into a jagged branch of sharpened coral. The coral branch impales the triggering creature, dealing @Damage[10d6[piercing]] damage (@Check[reflex|dc:44|basic] save). The triggering creature also takes @Damage[1d4[persistent,bleed]] damage on a critical failure. Regardless of the outcome, the coral then crumbles to dust.</p>"
